#: admin/admin-tpl/mascot-faq.php:109
msgid "Flush Rewrite Rules"
msgstr ""

#: admin/admin-tpl/mascot-faq.php:113
msgid ""
"Remove rewrite rules and then recreate rewrite rules. This method can be "
"used to refresh WordPress rewrite rule cache. Generally, this should be used "
"after programmatically adding one or more custom rewrite rules."
msgstr ""

#: admin/admin-tpl/mascot-faq.php:117
msgid "When it is necessary?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/admin-tpl/mascot-faq.php:119
msgid "-> Usually needs to flush rewrite rules for new custom post types."
msgstr ""

#: admin/admin-tpl/mascot-faq.php:121
msgid ""
"-> You should only flush rules on activation or deactivation of a plugin or "
"theme."
msgstr ""

#: admin/admin-tpl/mascot-faq.php:123
msgid ""
"-> If you get 404 Page not found error on some pages/posts that already "
"exist."
msgstr ""

#: admin/admin-tpl/mascot-faq.php:127
msgid "To flush WordPress rewrite rules or permalinks from the Dashboard:"
msgstr ""

#: admin/admin-tpl/mascot-faq.php:129
#, php-format
msgid "In the main menu find %1$sSettings > Permalinks%2$s"
msgstr ""

#: admin/admin-tpl/mascot-faq.php:131
msgid "2: Scroll down if needed and click Save Changes."
msgstr ""

#: admin/admin-tpl/mascot-faq.php:133
msgid "3: Rewrite rules and permalinks are flushed."
